From: Bogdan Hamciuc <bogdan.hamciuc@freescale.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Apr 2013 15:38:33 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 198/547] dpaa_eth: Switch compile default to "termination"

Switch the default compile option from "optimize for ipfwd" to "optimize
for termination".

Signed-off-by: Bogdan Hamciuc <bogdan.hamciuc@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I37b9b867b2f9787eb4a56a8005e198a2fb6430cc
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/1400
Reviewed-by: Radulescu Ruxandra Ioana-B05472 <ruxandra.radulescu@freescale.com>
Tested-by: Fleming Andrew-AFLEMING <AFLEMING@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Fleming Andrew-AFLEMING <AFLEMING@freescale.com>
[Original patch taken from QorIQ-SDK-V1.4-SOURCE-20130625-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Bin Jiang <bin.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
index 148adc5..1dbe8f1 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
@@ -28,7 +28,7 @@ config DPAA_ETH_SG_SUPPORT
 choice DPAA_ETH_OPTIMIZE
 	prompt "Optimization choices for the DPAA Ethernet driver"
 	depends on DPA_ETH
-	default DPAA_ETH_OPTIMIZE_FOR_IPFWD
+	default DPAA_ETH_OPTIMIZE_FOR_TERM
 	---help---
 	  Compile-time switch between driver optimizations for forwarding use-cases and
 	  termination scenarios.
